cs.ET, cs.LG, cs.EM, cs.SY, cs.AR

Reasoning: 
- cs.ET (Embedded Systems): The paper focuses on scheduling algorithms for intermittently powered embedded systems, which falls under the scope of cs.ET.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper proposes a semi-supervised machine learning model and discusses the trade-off between accuracy and execution time for deep neural networks, which falls under the scope of cs.LG.
- cs.EM (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the challenges and solutions for executing deep learning tasks on intermittently powered systems, which can be considered an emerging technology.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a scheduling algorithm for intermittently powered systems, which falls under the scope of cs.SY.
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the resource constraints of embedded platforms and proposes an imprecise computing-based scheduling algorithm, which falls under the scope of cs.AR.
